        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:35PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
St. Marys, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
St. Marys, Middlebourne, Paden City, Sistersville, Belmont, Newport,
Matamoras, Friendly, Fly, Alma, Arvilla, Point Lookout, New
Matamoras, and Wick.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
